This paper deals with the problem of multi-target tracking and data association in video, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper presents a novel algorithm for solving this problem using a column generation formulation, which is a common technique in optimization and operations research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also presents a relaxation of the combinatorial problem and uses dynamic programming to efficiently explore the space of tracks. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also deals with the problem of finding a maximum-weight set packing, which is a classic problem in combinatorial optimization. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which often deal with optimization problems.
